- **Title:** Therapeutic Targeting of CDK12/CDK13 in Triple-Negative Breast Cancer (PubMed)  
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/`  
  - **Direct quote snippets (identifiers / targets / modality / indication):**
    - “Here we report the development of SR-4835, a highly selective dual inhibitor of CDK12 and CDK13” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/?utm_source=openai))  
    - “which disables triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC) cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/31668947/?utm_source=openai))  

- **Title:** Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor (PubMed)  
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`  
  - **Direct quote snippets (identifiers / targets / modality / indication):**
    - “we have synthesized a potent PROTAC degrader PP-C8 based on the noncovalent dual inhibitors of CDK12/13” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/?utm_source=openai))  
    - “PP-C8 demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with PARP inhibitor in triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC).” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/?utm_source=openai))  

- **Title:** Discovery of a novel dual-target inhibitor of CDK12 and PARP1 that induces synthetic lethality for treatment of triple-negative breast cancer (PubMed)  
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37478560/`  
  - **Direct quote snippets (identifiers / targets / modality / indication):**
    - “The new dual-target inhibitor (12e) showed potent inhibitory activity against CDK12 (IC_{50} = 285 nM) and PARP1 (IC_{50} = 34 nM)” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37478560/?utm_source=openai))  
    - “Keywords: CDK12; Dual-target inhibitor; PARP1; Synthetic lethality; TNBC.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/37478560/?utm_source=openai))  

- **Title:** CDK12 Inhibition Reverses De Novo and Acquired PARP Inhibitor Resistance in BRCA Wild-Type and Mutated Models of Triple-Negative Breast Cancer (PubMed)  
  - **URL:** `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27880910/`
